        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="0">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove bellcrank relay lever, lower control rod and release lever. Retain mounting
                    hardware for re-use.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the new bellcrank relay lever with the long lever arm in the downward position.
                    Make sure the relay lever shaft rotates freely and the relay shaft is lubricated.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the new release shaft lever. Lubricate the cross shafts and check for free
                    rotation.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the new lower horizontal control rod with the forward end on the engine side of
                    the bellcrank relay lever and the rear end on the frame rail side of the release shaft lever.
                    Install the bolts pointing toward the engine.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify the 1/2 inch dimension from the clutch release bearing to the clutch brake.
                    Adjust the clutch internally if needed and lubricate the clutch release bearing. Refer to Group 11,
                    CTS-5043S, in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual for detailed clutch adjustment information.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify the 1/8 inch dimension between the release fork and the clutch release bearing
                    housing wear pads. To achieve the 1/8 inch dimension, the vertical clutch control rod may need to be
                    adjusted.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify the clutch pedal free travel is 2 inches. If necessary, adjust the clutch pedal
                    stop under the dash to achieve final adjustment.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>For SOLO clutch adjustment procedures refer to Group 11, CTS-5268, in the CTS-5000 Master
                        Service Manual.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
